name: Great Red Spot
description:
The Great Red Spot is a persistent high-pressure region in the atmosphere of Jupiter, producing an anticyclonic storm that is the largest in the Solar System.

The Great Red Spot is larger than the Earth , its stable and covers some part of jupiter's surface.

The composition and the source of its red color remain uncertain, although photodissociated ammonia reacting with acetylene is a robust candidate to explain the coloration.

Jupiter is one of my favorite planets , the greatest in our solar system.
